{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_89","type":"agent_message","text":"The diagnostic exposed the underlying behavior: this BlockHound build pulls in a shaded Byte Buddy version that does not officially support Java 25 unless `reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.experimental=true` is present as a startup VM property. That means the native `NoClassDefFoundError` stack is at least partly masking a class-initialization problem, not just a missing reflection entry. I’m reverting the temporary probe and checking how this repo normally handles Byte Buddy’s experimental flag in native tests before I decide whether the right fix is metadata-only or test/runtime configuration."}}
